The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Friday, June 04, 2004 				 Prices of 97 drugs revised
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								New Delhi, June 3: The National Pharmaceutical Pricing Authority (NPPA) has revised the prices of 97 formulation packs, including Glipizide and 17 packs of vitamin-based formulations, which would come into effect within a fortnight.																								Other drugs whose prices have been fixed by the NPPA include Carbamazepine 16 packs, Doxycycline 38 packs and three packs of Spironolactone.																								Also, prices have been revised for 20 non-ceiling packs (NCP), including bulk drug insulin, a combination of Cefotaxine Sodium, Aspirin, Sulbactum Sodium and PCMX drug.																								The prices fixed would become effective within 15 days from the date of notification in the official gazette or the receipt of the non-ceiling, price order of the NPPA in this regard, according to para 14(1) of Drugs Price Control Order (DPCO), 1995, the government said in a statement.																								While fixing these prices, the authority has also considered the additional packing material cost towards hologram labelling/ROPP Caps for prevention of spurious drugs, it said.																								The prices have been fixed in accordance with the provisions of the DPCO and the established criteria and guidelines, the statement added. 
